   "source": [
    "# What is the difference between yolort and yolov5\n",
    "\n",
    "Now `yolort` adopts the same model structure as the official `yolov5`. The main difference between yolort and YOLOv5 is the strategy in pre-processing and post-processing. The main reason we have adopted a different strategy from the official one is to enable the pre-processing and post-processing modules to be jit traceable and scriptable. From this we can gain an end-to-end Graph for inferencing on `LibTorch`, `ONNX Runtime` and `TVM`.\n",
    "\n",
    "For pre-processing, YOLOv5 uses the [letterboxing (padding)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Letterboxing_(filming)) resizing that maintains the aspect ratio. The error arises from the `interpolate` operator used in resizing. YOLOv5 uses the [cv2.resize](https://docs.opencv.org/4.x/da/d54/group__imgproc__transform.html#ga47a974309e9102f5f08231edc7e7529d) operator on the input `uint8 [0-255]` images, the operators in OpenCV are not traceable or scriptable, so we use [torch.nn.functional.interpolate](https://pytorch.org/docs/stable/generated/torch.nn.functional.interpolate.html#torch-nn-functional-interpolate) in yolort. Fortunately, the `interpolation` operator of PyTorch is [aligned](https://github.com/pytorch/vision/issues/2950#issuecomment-723038041) with that of OpenCV, however PyTorch's `interpolate` [only supports](https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/5580) the float data type now, we can only operate with images cast to float types, and therefore there will introduce some errors.\n",
    "\n",
    "YOLOv5 provides a very powerful function to do the post-processing, of which we implement only a non-agnostic version, but the accuracy here should be able to be consistent with the original version. See our [doc](https://zhiqwang.com/yolort/notebooks/how-to-align-with-ultralytics-yolov5.html) for more details.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Prepare environment, image and model weights to test"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "0622a4c5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import torch\n",
    "\n",
    "os.environ[\"CUDA_DEVICE_ORDER\"]=\"PCI_BUS_ID\"\n",
    "os.environ[\"CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES\"]=\"0\"\n",
    "\n",
    "device = torch.device('cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "aecd3da3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import cv2\n",
    "from yolort.models import YOLOv5\n",
    "from yolort.utils import Visualizer, cv2_imshow, read_image_to_tensor\n",
    "from yolort.utils.image_utils import parse_single_image\n",
    "from yolort.v5 import load_yolov5_model, letterbox, non_max_suppression, scale_coords, attempt_download\n",
    "from yolort.v5.utils.downloads import safe_download"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "c928a6a5-874b-4415-a2b3-9682cd1f6ad0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "img_size = 640\n",
    "stride = 64\n",
    "score_thresh = 0.35\n",
    "nms_thresh = 0.45\n",
    "fixed_shape = None"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "fd90859f-9fa2-411d-b391-7cabf7b2320c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Downloading https://huggingface.co/spaces/zhiqwang/assets/resolve/main/zidane.jpg to zidane.jpg...\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json": {
       "model_id": "b327c434960649fa95f12acbf950fca1",
       "version_major": 2,
       "version_minor": 0
      },
      "text/plain": [
       "  0%|          | 0.00/165k [00:00<?, ?B/s]"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# img_source = \"https://huggingface.co/spaces/zhiqwang/assets/resolve/main/bus.jpg\"\n",
    "img_source = \"https://huggingface.co/spaces/zhiqwang/assets/resolve/main/zidane.jpg\"\n",
    "img_path = img_source.split(\"/\")[-1]\n",
    "safe_download(img_path, img_source)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "8495e56f-b397-401a-ba13-1701fed3fdaa",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Downloaded from 'https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov5/releases/download/v6.1/yolov5s6.pt'\n",
    "model_path = 'yolov5s6.pt'\n",
    "checkpoint_path = attempt_download(model_path)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bc8fedc2-c9a1-4131-b7d9-fc07d878232d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Load model as ultralytics and inference\n",
    "\n",
    "YOLOv5 provides an input-robust model wrapper named `AutoShape` for passing cv2/np/PIL/torch inputs, which includes pre-processing, inference and post-processing (NMS). This wrapper is currently only valid for pytorch inference. To peel back the essence of what's inside, we use a vanilla interface to call yolov5. We do the pre-processing part first."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "d78f0b92-2350-480e-84c7-f6e61c3829f0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Preprocess\n",
    "img_raw = cv2.imread(img_path)\n",
    "\n",
    "img_shape = (img_size, img_size)\n",
    "auto_rectangle = not fixed_shape\n",
    "image = letterbox(img_raw, new_shape=img_shape, stride=stride, auto=auto_rectangle)[0]\n",
    "image = read_image_to_tensor(image)\n",
    "image = image.to(device)\n",
    "image = image[None]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "9ba2e63e-b2d7-4263-95f1-d5b80934d1c4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "vis = parse_single_image(image[0])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cc055937-c911-44c0-b990-14b4d6251a94",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let's visualize the letterboxed image by the way."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "79effda7-5897-4748-bc4f-baaccb9637cd",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<PIL.Image.Image image mode=RGB size=480x288 at 0x7F38D8BAD310>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "cv2_imshow(vis, imshow_scale=0.75, convert_bgr_to_rgb=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "12385399",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "model_yolov5 = load_yolov5_model(checkpoint_path)\n",
    "model_yolov5 = model_yolov5.to(device)\n",
    "model_yolov5 = model_yolov5.eval()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "670dfa9d-7828-4b32-9d3e-97c89ffab27d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "/opt/conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/torch/functional.py:445: UserWarning: torch.meshgrid: in an upcoming release, it will be required to pass the indexing argument. (Triggered internally at  ../aten/src/ATen/native/TensorShape.cpp:2157.)\n",
      "  return _VF.meshgrid(tensors, **kwargs)  # type: ignore[attr-defined]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "    yolov5_dets = model_yolov5(image)\n",
    "    yolov5_dets = non_max_suppression(yolov5_dets, score_thresh, nms_thresh, agnostic=False)[0]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "594b68e0-5fe6-4886-baf3-79716dc7301f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Then restore the coordinates to the original scale of the image."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "88616c69-9530-4472-9e51-70628bf527c2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "boxes_yolov5 = scale_coords(image.shape[2:], yolov5_dets[:, :4], img_raw.shape[:-1])\n",
    "labels_yolov5 = yolov5_dets[:, 5].to(dtype=torch.int64)\n",
    "scores_yolov5 = yolov5_dets[:, 4]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0b772e20-fdf3-4664-a48d-5bbb0ab037df",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "c682c704-9077-4105-8608-4bf64accb71e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Downloading https://huggingface.co/spaces/zhiqwang/assets/resolve/main/coco.names to coco.names...\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json": {
       "model_id": "7ef1b9f5ce4945a0b285710d5ff8d6c0",
       "version_major": 2,
       "version_minor": 0
      },
      "text/plain": [
       "  0%|          | 0.00/621 [00:00<?, ?B/s]"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "label_source = \"https://huggingface.co/spaces/zhiqwang/assets/resolve/main/coco.names\"\n",
    "label_path = label_source.split(\"/\")[-1]\n",
    "safe_download(label_path, label_source)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "e2c98eee",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<PIL.Image.Image image mode=RGB size=640x360 at 0x7F38D8B9AD90>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "v = Visualizer(img_raw, metalabels=label_path)\n",
    "# Prepare the prediction labels for the Visualizer\n",
    "predictions = {\"boxes\": boxes_yolov5, \"labels\": labels_yolov5, \"scores\": scores_yolov5}\n",
    "v.draw_instance_predictions(predictions)\n",
    "v.imshow(scale=0.5)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f028a350-2c26-4dc4-be62-a1a6a9b19084",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "At that moment we have completed the whole inference process of yolov5.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Use yolort's approach to inferencing\n",
    "\n",
    "yolort now supports loading models trained by yolov5. Here is also an end-to-end inference pipeline, and this pipeline supports both jit tracing and scripting modes. This model can be used to export ONNX and torchscript graph and to inference on ONNX Runtime, LibTorch and TVM VirtualMachine backends."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "7d731f3c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "model_yolort = YOLOv5.load_from_yolov5(\n",
    "    checkpoint_path,\n",
    "    score_thresh=score_thresh,\n",
    "    nms_thresh=nms_thresh,\n",
    "    size_divisible=stride,\n",
    "    fixed_shape=fixed_shape,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "model_yolort = model_yolort.eval()\n",
    "model_yolort = model_yolort.to(device)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "91437d59-ffa3-433b-8167-bab79330f153",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Its interface is also very easy to use."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "id": "abf294ac-a562-43b2-ac45-a335b5b8f6fd",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "    yolort_dets = model_yolort.predict(img_path)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "id": "5c0f6c99-2b75-4436-aae0-f7c746f66d62",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "boxes_yolort = yolort_dets[0]['boxes']\n",
    "labels_yolort = yolort_dets[0]['labels']\n",
    "scores_yolort = yolort_dets[0]['scores']"
   ]
  },
  {
